                          July 15 (Bloomberg) -- American International Group Inc. Chairman Harvey Golub stepped down from the bailed-out insurer after feuding with Chief Executive Officer Robert Benmosche over the stalled divestiture of an Asia division. Bloomberg's Sheila Dharmarajan reports. (Source: Bloomberg)  
                           

     
